                        .ui.basic.card
                            .content
                                h2 
                                    span#narrate-slide-header-types-3 Online
                                p#narrate-1-types-3
                                    span Scammers often mimic a legitimate site or email address by using a slight variation in spelling. 
                                    span#narrate-2-types-3 
                                        span Or an email may look like it came from a legitimate company, but the actual email address is suspicious.
                                    span#narrate-3-types-3 
                                        span For example, this email's address "walmrt@gmail.com" has a misspelling of "walmart". 
                                    span#narrate-4-types-3 
                                        span Therefore, the email is not from the company's site.      
